features: THE STRONGEST, WINDPROOF & BEAUTIFUL, LIGHTWEIGHT UMBRELLA: Tired of getting soaked in the rain due to a broken or bent umbrella? No more! Tumella Is in a class of its own. UPGRADED & UNMATCHED WIND AND WATER PROTECTION: Waterproof coating shields you from bad weather. We added a vented double canopy that allows wind to pass through, to securely and conveniently withstand even the harshest weather (tested in the university of Eindhoven at 70+MPH wind tunnel - equivalent to type 1 hurricane, see video). SUPERIOR STURDINESS & LIFETIME REPLACEMENT: Unlike regular umbrellas with only 6 to 9 weak aluminum or resin-reinforced ribs, Tumella has 9 fiberglass ribs made specifically with the new and superior ultra-flex 2025 tech, making it almost unbreakable when it bends under heavy wind conditions (while retaining it’s shape and full functionality afterward). The last umbrella you'll need to buy.

LIGHTWEIGHT, EASY ONE-HANDED USE, SMALL & PORTABLE: Take this compact umbrella for travel with you wherever you go. So versatile and simple to use, with just the touch of a button, you can automatically open or close your Tumella. It fits perfectly in your backpack, purse, or car door, with just 11 by 2.75 inches in size, weights less than 1 lb, while offering a huge coverage of 42 inch.

40+ UNIQUE, VIBRANT & BEAUTIFUL GIFT IDEAS: Dress up your look with a unique companion umbrella. Choose from our vibrant selection of elegant and nature-based designs. Enjoy long-lasting, high-quality printed art while protected from the elements. Gift your loved ones a Tumella (or a few), a superior and fashionable travel umbrella for all seasons and all weather.

WE OFFER LIFELONG CARE AND SUPPORT if you ever have a concern with your Tumella. We want it to be your go-to for years to come—rain or shine. That’s why every part is carefully selected, thoroughly tested, and thoughtfully assembled to meet our high standards of durability and style.

Upgrade Your Wearing Experience

1. Sports enthusiasts: occasional joggers, runners, gym goers, committed marathon and triathlon athletes

FAQ

1. What if I don't like the color?

Our images are shot by DSLR, and while we've done our best, there are inevitably slight color difference, due to lighting and camera settings.

If you are not satisfied with the color you get,we will provide refund or free replacement.

It is simple. Every pack comes with instruction and there is video in this page.

3. Can I reopen the clip?

Yes, you can. First insert a small flat head / minus screwdriver to the groove at the bottom of the clip, rotate the screwdriver a bit and the clip opens.

4. Are these long enough for boots?

They are 120cm long and will fit most ankle-top boots. However, if your boots are higher or oversize, we recommend doing a measurement before placing the order, or have a look at our RJ-Sport No Tie Boots Laces.

5. How thick are these laces?

They are 3.0mm thick and should fit most shoes, but please have a check if your shoes have small eyelets.

productDetails.description:
HOW SHOULD I CARE FOR MY SWIMSUITS?

Swimsuits are afraid of heat

Many people are afraid that there will be bacteria on their swimsuits after swimming, and they like to wash them with hot water. High temperature will destroy the material of the swimsuit, denature the elastic material, and the swimsuits will gradually lose their elasticity. So, you only need to wash the swimming trunks with cold or warm water

Clean swimsuits with neutral detergent

After changing the swimsuits, we rinse them with clean water first, and then soak them in some neutral detergents such as shower gel and shampoo, and then gently wash and rinse with hands.

Don't wring out swimming trunks too hard

Tightly wringing out with your hands or using a washing machine to dry the swimsuits will damage the fabric fibers of the swimming trunks and cause damage. It is recommended to lay the swimsuit flat on a dry towel or dry it in a cool place. (Don't expose it to the sun)
